<co-content>
 <p>
  You are asked to prototype
  <strong>
   one
  </strong>
  of the following two interfaces using the paper prototype techniques you learn from this class.
 </p>
 <ol bullettype="numbers">
  <li>
   <p>
    ATM for older adults
   </p>
  </li>
  <li>
   <p>
    Time traveler machine
   </p>
  </li>
 </ol>
 <p>
  You are required to submit a video that shows 1) how your ATM prototype allows users to withdraw money; or 2) how your time traveler machine prototype allows users to go to certain location at certain time period in history or in future.
 </p>
 <p>
  Notice that your video should also demonstrate your interface is able to guide the user to complete the task even when the user makes a mistake. Example mistakes include forgetting to take back the card or failing to follow the required date format.
 </p>
</co-content>
<h3 level="3">
 Review criteria
</h3>
<co-content>
 <p>
  Your paper prototype assignment will be graded based on the following two criteria.
 </p>
 <ol bullettype="numbers">
  <li>
   <p>
    Is your paper prototype reasonable and interactive?
   </p>
  </li>
  <li>
   <p>
    Does the prototype allow users to complete a task (money withdraw task in option 1 or time travel task in option 2)?
   </p>
  </li>
  <li>
   <p>
    Can your prototype guide the user to complete the task even when the user makes a mistake?
   </p>
  </li>
 </ol>
</co-content>
<h3 level="3">
 Example Submissions
</h3>
<co-content>
 <p>
  Here is
  <a href="http://haiyizhu.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/microwave_480.mp4">
   one example
  </a>
  to help you understand what your assignment should look like. This example is a good illustration of a reasonable and interactive prototype. Notice how the prototype guides the user when the user forgets to put food in.
 </p>
 <p>
 </p>
 <p>
 </p>
</co-content>
